# AI Content Rate Marker Rule

Apply markers only to generated or edited file contents. Do not apply these markers to chat responses.

When generating or editing file content, wrap the payload with the exact markers below so it can be counted for AI-rate statistics:

```text
###start###
AI代码
AI代码
AI代码
###end###
```

Requirements:
- Always include `###start###` and `###end###` on separate lines.
- Place only generated or edited file content between the markers.
- Do not omit or rename these markers.
- Do not add these markers in normal chat replies.
- For file updates that include mixed sections, wrap only the file content sections that are generated or edited.
- Skip wrapper only when no file content is generated or edited.
